I emphatically oppose Secretary Nielsen’s call to expedite the deportation of innocent children for whom America is their best hope for survival.  Our laws should protect children, not threaten their safety. https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/immigration/dhs-ask-congress-sweeping-authority-deport-unaccompanied-migrant-children-n988651 …

Imagine the hopelessness & helplessness that these migrant families must feel, as the cries of caged children and the screams of captive babies echo against the bridge and throughout the holding pen. This administration’s treatment of migrants is beneath all standards of decency.

Imagine enduring danger and abuse on the journey to our border, because you literally have no other choice if you want to survive.  Then, imagine finally getting to America’s border, only to be caged behind chain-link fencing under a bridge.

If you're having trouble empathizing with the plight of migrants, I ask you to imagine having no choice but to flee your home country – leaving behind everyone and everything you know – because it’s your only chance to stay alive, or the only way to protect your children.

As DHS Appropriations chair, I am closely monitoring the humanitarian crisis at the border, and will quickly review and respond to any emergency supplemental appropriations request to help DHS respond. We must ensure migrants in U.S. custody are kept safe and treated properly.

Some in this administration may be blind to the awful plight of the migrants trapped at the center of the humanitarian crisis on our border, but I cannot and will not ignore these frightened, suffering families. https://roybal-allard.house.gov/news/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=398577 …
